#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:2 d73c528bc2114e4388a7d1e65991b6d1
msgid "GitHub Issues"
msgstr "GitHub Issues"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:4 922694a425c543d288af7ea1a2f3fb17
msgid ""
"The issue tracker is for **confirmed bugs** and **concrete feature "
"requests** — things a maintainer (or you) could in principle act on by "
"writing code. Open-ended questions, design discussion, and \"how do I do X\""
" belong on :doc:`github_discussions` or :doc:`discord` instead; the new-"
"issue chooser will offer those routes alongside the templates."
msgstr ""
"issue 跟踪器用于\\ **已确认的缺陷**\\ 和\\ "
"**具体的功能请求**——也就是维护者（或您）原则上可以通过编写代码来处理的事项。开放式的问题、设计讨论以及\"我该如何做 X\"之类的内容则应放到 "
":doc:`github_discussions` 或 :doc:`discord`\\ ；新建 issue 的选择器会在模板之外一并提供这些途径。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:12
#: b7e14b2012ea4823a9850ebde2da3cc5
msgid "Open an issue"
msgstr "提交 issue"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:29
#: f0a594b8d95e44a4aa5e471baf61e493
msgid ""
"Clicking the link above takes you to the *new-issue chooser* — a menu with "
"two templates and three \"you probably want to go elsewhere\" shortcuts:"
msgstr "点击上方链接会进入\\ *新建 issue 选择器*——这是一个菜单，包含两个模板和三个\"您可能想去别处\"的快捷入口："

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:37
#: 7bb7677c9ebc40d3bfbf584dfa505fe5
msgid "Choice"
msgstr "选项"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:38
#: e19692c9c9e1416ea7cdab1eb45ddbab
msgid "When to pick it"
msgstr "何时选择它"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:39
#: 58a9e14674204ff999ef6a786f948310
msgid "🐛 **Bug Report**"
msgstr "🐛 **Bug Report**"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:40
#: f41d6b1c40284995ab7d0ce27999081f
msgid "Something is broken or wrong. You can reproduce it."
msgstr "某处出现故障或错误，并且您能够复现它。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:41
#: fc38de85d5924771bb7cda2ab589fdce
msgid "✨ **Feature Request**"
msgstr "✨ **Feature Request**"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:42
#: 3aae25f4a71f4fd0ba1ec3067b3d8bae
msgid "You want a specific, well-scoped addition or change."
msgstr "您希望增加或更改某项具体、范围明确的内容。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:43
#: 036aacbbb6a84c4db8a5a3e88776f85c
msgid "💬 Usage question"
msgstr "💬 使用问题"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:44
#: d30063d99c6149a484fc5facd31005c9
msgid "Redirects to **Discussions Q&A** — not an issue."
msgstr "重定向至 **Discussions Q&A**——而非 issue。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:45
#: 5b3a4386deac4ab7836d2e0f035d4082
msgid "💡 Idea or proposal"
msgstr "💡 想法或提案"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:46
#: 597307e676164fa785cc6605fb269b44
msgid "Redirects to **Discussions Ideas & RFCs** — not an issue."
msgstr "重定向至 **Discussions Ideas & RFCs**——而非 issue。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:47
#: 536043f7d79f453f8d6fea573b63aded
msgid "🗨️ Real-time chat"
msgstr "🗨️ 实时交流"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:48
#: 07829238ab0544e4ba839f29db65bc94
msgid "Redirects to **Discord**."
msgstr "重定向至 **Discord**\\ 。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:50
#: b5b831b457c44495a34dae8c7ac87579
msgid ""
"Blank issues are disabled — every issue starts from a template, which keeps "
"triage tractable."
msgstr "已禁用空白 issue——每个 issue 都从模板开始，这样可以让分类整理保持井然有序。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:55
#: f084f634708d4e22ba14401c1c57db5f
msgid "What each template captures"
msgstr "每个模板收集哪些信息"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:57
#: 58b025309d4c4e278d378ae47a53a6f5
msgid ""
"Both templates are GitHub *issue forms*: structured fields with validation, "
"rendered as a form rather than free-form Markdown. Required fields are "
"clearly marked."
msgstr ""
"两个模板都是 GitHub 的 *issue 表单*\\ ：带有校验的结构化字段，以表单形式而非自由的 Markdown "
"形式呈现。必填字段都有清晰标注。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:61
#: de6da06eb8a9491295cf50c30bdc50b2
msgid ""
"**🐛 Bug Report** — required fields are *Description*, *Minimal reproducing "
"example*, *Expected behavior*, *Environment*, plus two pre-flight "
"checkboxes. The full traceback is optional (some bugs produce a wrong result"
" rather than an exception). The environment field tells you exactly what to "
"paste:"
msgstr ""
"**🐛 Bug Report**——必填字段为 *Description*\\ （描述）、\\ *Minimal reproducing "
"example*\\ （最小复现示例）、\\ *Expected behavior*\\ （期望行为）、\\ *Environment*\\ "
"（环境），外加两个提交前的勾选项。完整的回溯信息是可选的（有些缺陷产生的是错误结果而非异常）。环境字段会明确告诉您应粘贴哪些内容："

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:77
#: f8474e356c5a411bb36c7db15f475c01
msgid ""
"If you can't fill out the *Minimal reproducing example*, that usually means "
"the problem isn't reduced enough yet — try to shrink it before filing. A "
"200-line script and a five-line script take roughly the same amount of human"
" attention to read, and the five-line script is ten times more likely to get"
" a fast answer."
msgstr ""
"如果您填不出 *Minimal reproducing example*\\ ，这通常意味着问题还没有被充分简化——请在提交前尝试将其缩小。一个 200"
" 行的脚本和一个五行的脚本，让人阅读时所需的精力大致相同，而五行的脚本得到快速答复的可能性要高出十倍。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:83
#: 647d1a69f5c545c2aed81d24369d79a7
msgid ""
"**✨ Feature Request** — only *Use case* is strictly required. Lead with the "
"**motivation** (\"I'm trying to solve X\") rather than a proposed API "
"(\"please add ``foo``\"). A clear use case lets the maintainers and the "
"community shape the API together; a pre-specified API often anchors the "
"discussion in the wrong place."
msgstr ""
"**✨ Feature Request**——只有 *Use case*\\ （用例）是严格必填的。请以\\ **动机**\\ （\"我想要解决 "
"X\"）作为开头，而不是预设的 API（\"请添加 ``foo``\"）。清晰的用例能让维护者和社区一同塑造 API；而预先指定的 API "
"往往会把讨论锚定在错误的方向上。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:91
#: 7470c052039a4d2993158730fa31c6c1
msgid "What happens after you file"
msgstr "提交之后会发生什么"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:93
#: 2f1723c2de4443a3844483908cad31ea
msgid "The basic shape:"
msgstr "基本流程如下："

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:95
#: d31bd735db314afbbf8af6e30772215d
msgid ""
"**Auto-label** — every new issue lands with the ``triage`` label plus its "
"category (``bug`` or ``enhancement``), set by the template."
msgstr ""
"**自动打标签**——每个新 issue 都会带有 ``triage`` 标签，以及由模板设定的类别标签（\\ ``bug`` 或 "
"``enhancement``\\ ）。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:98
#: 658b0e8d30dc4d9f869d0ec237b152a6
msgid ""
"**Triage** — a maintainer reads it, possibly asks for more info, removes "
"``triage`` once the report is actionable, and adds topic labels (e.g. "
"``meshing``, ``solver``, ``cuda``) so similar issues cluster together."
msgstr ""
"**分类整理**——维护者会阅读它，可能会要求补充更多信息，在报告变得可处理后移除 ``triage`` 标签，并添加主题标签（例如 "
"``meshing``\\ 、\\ ``solver``\\ 、\\ ``cuda``\\ ），以便相似的 issue 聚集在一起。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:102
#: 021a755eada2486cb4e87eafb68bf68e
msgid "**Disposition** — one of:"
msgstr "**处置结果**——为以下之一："

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:104
#: f3f8a4b828ee41e0a5f270794e62cd65
msgid ""
"Confirmed and queued for work (someone will pick it up; you are welcome to "
"too — see :doc:`contributing`)."
msgstr "已确认并排入待处理队列（会有人来接手；也欢迎您自己来处理——参见 :doc:`contributing`\\ ）。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:106
#: b3d60261f9b04716aaa93ae32a57fc17
msgid ""
"Asked for clarification (please respond; stale issues with no follow-up may "
"be closed)."
msgstr "要求进一步澄清（请予以回复；长期无人跟进的陈旧 issue 可能会被关闭）。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:108
#: abbbc69b4e7d4a2580524bce97f359f5
msgid "Closed as a duplicate, invalid, or \"won't fix\" with an explanation."
msgstr "因重复、无效或\"不予修复\"而关闭，并附上说明。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:111
#: 8ae113394b4a46df921d14e9bac8e5bc
msgid ""
"This is a research-affiliated project with a small maintainer team — "
"response times are best-effort, not contractual. If your issue is urgent for"
" a paper deadline, mention it in the description; if it has been silent for "
"more than two weeks, a polite ping is welcome."
msgstr ""
"这是一个隶属于科研机构的项目，维护团队规模很小——响应时间为尽力而为，并非合同义务。如果您的 issue "
"因论文截止日期而紧急，请在描述中说明；如果它沉寂了两周以上，欢迎礼貌地提醒一下。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:118
#: 517116e1b197464fa6a7747a2a92a08a
msgid "Before you file: search first"
msgstr "提交之前：请先搜索"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:120
#: 6022d56022154a66a928a4e497652811
msgid ""
"A 30-second search avoids most duplicates and often turns up an existing "
"workaround. Useful entry points:"
msgstr "花 30 秒搜索一下，就能避免大多数重复，而且往往能找到现成的变通办法。有用的入口："

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:123
#: 89e2eba767dc425787272a807e809f1e
msgid ""
"Open + closed issues, scoped to this repo: ``https://github.com/camlab-"
"ethz/TensorMesh/issues?q=<terms>`` (drop the default ``is:open`` to include "
"closed ones)."
msgstr ""
"限定在本仓库范围内、包含未关闭与已关闭的 issue：\\ ``https://github.com/camlab-"
"ethz/TensorMesh/issues?q=<terms>``\\ （去掉默认的 ``is:open`` 即可一并包含已关闭的 issue）。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:126
#: a40bcc53971e4be19fd9286345d55a62
msgid ""
"Discussions — usage questions and design conversations live there, not here."
msgstr "Discussions——使用问题和设计讨论位于那里，而非这里。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:128
#: 0decdc7621e64d79a6e4fd894ecbb199
msgid ""
"Google with a ``site:`` filter: ``site:github.com/camlab-ethz/TensorMesh "
"<your terms>``."
msgstr ""
"使用带 ``site:`` 过滤器的 Google 搜索：\\ ``site:github.com/camlab-ethz/TensorMesh "
"<your terms>``\\ 。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:131
#: 4b4a063d4518426eaf851322c61d4a79
msgid ""
"If you find a related issue but yours is genuinely different, link to it "
"from your new issue (\"related to #NN, but X is different\") — that helps "
"triage decide whether to merge them."
msgstr ""
"如果您找到一个相关的 issue，但您的问题确实有所不同，请在您的新 issue 中关联它（\"与 #NN 相关，但 X "
"不同\"）——这有助于分类整理时判断是否应将它们合并。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:137
#: 3f87cdf960ca4eeea0bc0b77ffde4908
msgid "From Discussion to Issue"
msgstr "从 Discussion 到 Issue"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:139
#: 162decf689e04b56bea7c768622bfe8c
msgid "Issues and Discussions cross over in two natural directions:"
msgstr "Issue 和 Discussion 会在两个自然的方向上相互转化："

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:141
#: c67f84595b2c46dc8413bd4e053ee72c
msgid ""
"**Q&A → Bug.** A \"how do I…\" question on Discussions Q&A turns out to be a"
" real bug. Open an issue, reference the discussion thread for context "
"(``Discussion: #DD``), and link the issue back from the discussion. Don't "
"re-paste the whole transcript."
msgstr ""
"**Q&A → Bug。** Discussions 问答区里一个\"我该如何……\"的问题最终被证实是一个真正的缺陷。请提交一个 "
"issue，引用该讨论帖以提供背景（\\ ``Discussion: #DD``\\ ），并从讨论帖中反向链接到该 "
"issue。不要把整段对话再粘贴一遍。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:145
#: 6d64b990504443f19ab91c26c7f46e65
msgid ""
"**Idea & RFC → Feature.** After a design discussion converges, file an issue"
" (or a PR) with the agreed design in the description, and link the "
"discussion thread. The issue is then the *commitment*; the discussion is the"
" *deliberation*."
msgstr ""
"**Idea & RFC → Feature。** 当一场设计讨论达成共识后，提交一个 issue（或一个 "
"PR），在描述中写明商定的设计，并链接到该讨论帖。此时 issue 即是\\ *正式承诺*\\ ，而讨论则是\\ *审议过程*\\ 。"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:152
#: fc8aa62d3b7247fa846a700845ea9c11
msgid "Pull requests"
msgstr "拉取请求"

#: ../../source/community/github_issues.rst:154
#: b184f312fd894ccd972dd697e458ecfa
msgid ""
"This page is about *filing* issues. If you want to *fix* one, the PR "
"workflow — dev environment, branch naming, tests, doc updates — lives in "
":doc:`contributing`. Linking the PR to its issue (``Fixes #NN`` in the "
"description) auto-closes the issue on merge, which the triage flow above "
"relies on."
msgstr ""
"本页讲的是\\ *提交* issue。如果您想\\ *修复*\\ 某个 issue，PR 的工作流程——开发环境、分支命名、测试、文档更新——都在 "
":doc:`contributing` 中。将 PR 关联到对应的 issue（在描述中写 ``Fixes #NN``\\ ）会在合并时自动关闭该 "
"issue，而上文的分类整理流程正依赖于这一点。"
